    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="oh-well-it-should-be-latex">Oh well, it should be latex.</h1>

<p>I used this post: <a href="http://chuchao333.github.io/blog/2012/08/18/supporting-latex-in-octopress/">supporting latex in octopress</a></p>

<p>To enable this, I used kramdown and mathjax, look at <a href="://jeffvautin.com/blog/2012/12/30/changing-the-octopress-markdown-engine/">changing markdown to kramdown http</a></p>

<p>Here is a very simple example of latex:</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
 \xi = 15 \\
 \frac{d^2f}{dx^2} = 6xf - 88
</script>

<p>I love writing articles in latex and after writing some recently, I thought about reposting it here.
Now I have my tools. Stay tuned.</p>
